{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LTPvnFMcJrj5tvVoepc7dg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Workflows\n     2→\n     3→Cloche workflows define a directed graph of steps connected by named results.\n     4→\n     5→## Workflow Locations\n     6→\n     7→Cloche distinguishes two workflow locations based on the file they live in:\n     8→\n     9→**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) — Run inside a Docker\n    10→container via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type. These are the\n    11→standard workflows for coding tasks.\n    12→\n    13→**Host workflows** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — Run on the host machine as the daemon\n    14→process. Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow` step type\n    15→dispatches a container workflow run and waits for it to complete. This is the extension\n    16→point for custom orchestration strategies.\n    17→\n    18→A single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n    19→uses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n    20→\n    21→| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n    22→|-------|--------------|---------|\n    23→| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n    24→| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n    25→| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n    26→\n    27→Only `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a legacy\n    28→single-function mode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n    29→\n    30→The `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n    31→object with the following fields:\n    32→\n    33→| Field | Required | Description |\n    34→|-------|----------|-------------|\n    35→| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n    36→| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n    37→| `title` | no | Short summary |\n    38→| `description` | no | Full description |\n    39→| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n    40→\n    41→The daemon picks the first task with status `open` (or empty, for backward\n    42→compatibility), runs `main` with that task ID, then runs `finalize` with the outcome.\n    43→Tasks are deduplicated within a configurable timeout window to prevent rapid\n    44→reassignment.\n    45→\n    46→The convention is enforced at parse time: a `workflow_name` step in a container workflow\n    47→file is a parse error.\n    48→\n    49→## Concepts\n    50→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SomgMrhxSEJYZQytifupGM","session_id":"5c40c135-d6d6-46ff-91b7-1e8ee6d44e10","uuid":"b1b311cb-787d-4e3f-b5ed-2e99952408c0"}
